in hyprland. I just pressed some key combo - don't know which - and my browser seemed to vanish. i had lots of valuable tabs open. how do I get them back

Don't panic! In Hyprland, it is much more likely that your browser has been "hidden" or moved rather than actually closed. Because Hyprland is a dynamic tiling compositor, windows usually only disappear if they are moved to a different workspace, toggled into a special "scratchpad," or minimized.

Here are the most likely ways to find your lost browser:

1. Check the Special Workspace (Scratchpad)
Many Hyprland configs use a "special" workspace as a scratchpad for things like terminals or browsers. If you accidentally hit Super + S (or whatever your config uses for togglespecialworkspace), your browser might be sitting in a hidden layer.

Action: Try pressing Super + S (or your configured scratchpad toggle) to see if it reappears.

2. Check Other Workspaces
It’s very easy to accidentally "send" a window to another workspace.

Action: Use Super + 1 through 0 to cycle through your workspaces.

Pro Tip: If you have a bar like Waybar, look at the workspace icons. If a workspace number is highlighted or has a dot under it, there’s a window living there.

3. Cycle Through Windows
If the browser is just buried under another window in "fullscreen" or "tabbed" mode:

Action: Use your focus keys (usually Super + Left/Right or Super + H/L) to see if the focus frame moves to an "invisible" window.

4. Check if it's "Floating" or Minimized
While Hyprland doesn't have a traditional "taskbar" minimize, some scripts or custom configs implement a hide/minimize feature.

Action: Open your terminal and type:

Bash
hyprctl clients
This will list every open window. Look for your browser (e.g., class: google-chrome or class: firefox). If it appears in this list, look at the workspace: line to see exactly where Hyprland thinks it is.

If the browser actually crashed or closed...
If hyprctl clients doesn't show your browser, the process might have died.

The "Undo" Button: Re-open the browser. Almost all modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Brave) will detect an "improper exit" and show a bar at the top saying: "Browser didn't shut down correctly. Restore Pages?"

History Shortcut: If that doesn't appear, press Ctrl + Shift + T. This is the universal shortcut to "Reopen Closed Tab." If the whole window closed, this will often bring back the entire window with all tabs intact.

